            <biogHist>
                <p>Reverend Dr Kenneth MacLeod, born in 1871 and originally from Eigg, served as
                    Church of Scotland minister in Colonsay and Gigha. In addition to writing his
                    own Gaelic prose and song, he collected Gaelic folklore and folk songs. In 1909,
                    he collaborated with Mrs Kennedy Fraser in <span localType="mods-titleinfo"
                        >Songs of the Hebrides</span>. He died in 1955.</p>
